Isn't there still an argument to be made for changing the paradigm of how outside academia looks at LA?

Digital worlds allow more voices, otherwise not heard by academia, to speak and as a result
better demonstrate LA's regional diversity. Methods for examining cultural phenomena of 
these voices become all the more important.

What about approaching it as purely literary?
Was LA ever literarily homogenous?

What are the boundaries of "imagined" community/region


